			<title>EverQuest EQ N beta signups (for European players wanting to register their old account)</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?75629-EQ-N-beta-signups-(for-European-players-wanting-to-register-their-old-account)&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sun, 11 Aug 2013 08:02:16 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>Made a new thread for this as I am not sure how many follow the EQ thread which is just speculation mostly. 
 
Go to soe.com 
 
Log in with the account you wish to apply for beta with. 
 
Copy paste the link below and add the h infront of ttps (removed it because it kept resetting to a shortened...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Made a new thread for this as I am not sure how many follow the EQ thread which is just speculation mostly.<br />
<br />
Go to soe.com<br />
<br />
Log in with the account you wish to apply for beta with.<br />
<br />
Copy paste the link below and add the h infront of ttps (removed it because it kept resetting to a shortened url link)<br />
<br />
ttps://account.station.sony.com/authenticated/beta/signUpForBetaRedirect.action?theme=eql&amp;betaId=17&amp;s  ervice=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.everquestnext.com%2fbeta-registration<br />
<br />
press enter.<br />
<br />
Will then get the normal &quot;do you wish to use NA/EU&quot; window popup. Pick whatever. The link above will automatically register you for beta. Should get an email confirmation immediately. So if there are any bonuses from having played EQ before (such as preferred Beta access or in game goodies) then you will now be able to get them. And you do not have to deal with whatever company is doing the EU side (+ double beta chance if you already registered a new account to apply for the EU beta)</div>

